title: @SC_Varsity Highlights of the Day for Oct. 9
text: Posted Oct. 9, 2015 at 11:58 PM Posted Oct. 9, 2015 at 11:58 PM » Social News Follow us on Twitter to get story updates, sports scores and highlights of the day! @SCTSPORTS Follow us on Twitter for all the latest insight from our team of professional beat writers and award-winning columnists! MVP Bailey Peach, Dartmouth Played a good all-around match for the Indians in a 25-23, 25-18, 26-24 volleyball win at New Bedford on Friday. Finished with 15 kills, 15 service points, 11 digs and six aces for Dartmouth (11-1, 1-1 Old Colony League), which completed its first regular-season sweep over the Whalers in the five years that Rachel Lassey has been coaching the team. QUOTABLE “I believe this will be a momentum game for us. They got their feet wet. They’re really playing hard, but they know how it feels now (to score goals). I don’t think they’re going to give up.”--Wareham field hockey coach Suzanne Modlowski, after her team scored twice in a 2-2 tie with Case. The 0-9-1 Vikings had scored just one goal in the nine games prior, and it came all the way back in the season opener. NUMBER TO KNOW 105 Total passing yards between Apponequet, Wareham, Bishop Stang and Martha's Vineyard during a rain-soaked Friday night. The Lakers threw for 42 yards, the Vikings threw for 38 and the Vineyard threw for 25. Stang didn't complete a pass. TODAY'S GAMES Sandwich at Bishop Stang - 3:30 p.m. Attleboro at New Bedford - 11 a.m. Field Hockey Apponequet at Bishop Stang - 10 a.m. Needham at Dartmouth - 12 p.m. Westport at Tiverton, RI - 10:30 a.m. Football Nantucket at Old Colony - 1 p.m. Bridgewater-Raynham at Dartmouth - 12 p.m. Fairhaven at GNB Voc-Tech - 12 p.m. New Bedford at Barrington, RI - 11 a.m. Girls Soccer New Bedford at Attleboro - 11 a.m. Dartmouth at Somerset Berkley - 12 p.m. HARLEM WIZARDS The Harlem Wizards will play a visit to New Bedford High School at 7 p.m. on Thursday to raise funds for New Bedford High girls basketball and field hockey and the New Bedford police union.The Wizards will take on a team made up of district teachers, including Brian Rudolph, and police officers. Pre-sale tickets are $8 for students and $13 for adults and can be purchased at COrner Sports, Amaral's Market and Johna's Hair Salon or at harlemwizards.com . Tickets at the door are $10 for students and $15 for adults. Reserved seating (first two rows) is $20 and comes with a poster. Courtside Plus tickets are on the court and cost $25. CORSAIRS Football falls to BSU The UMass Dartmouth football team trailed 14-13 in the third quarter before Bridgewater State scored the final 20 points in a 34-14 rain-delayed victory Friday night. The Corsairs fell to 3-3, while BSU moved to 4-2. Cory Burnham threw for 168 yards for UMD, which got 80 rushing yards from Eddie Sheriden and 103 receiving yards from Jason Ferri. southcoasttoday.com
